#### cat prints the contents of one or more files
#### ls shows possible arguments, ls -a shows the hidden files (files that begin with ".")
#### touch creates an empty file
#### rm deletes a file
#### find commands returns all files if given wihtout an argument. If given with an argument (eg. '-name'), it returns the search results based on that criteria.
# Linking
## Hard Links
#### Hard Link is a pointer to the inode of the file.
#### Syntax: ln orignal_file hard_link_name
## Soft Links
#### soft link is a pointer to the file name.
#### Syntax: ln -s file_name link_name
